			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: hardcore 1-65 without 2-boxing<a name="28334"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 17 04 10:59 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sounds legit. Four years ago I was trying to get 8 characters to 50 when I started, but then life changed and I'd rather spend the time with my two boys ages 1 and 3. With that kind of plat, your are looking at an easy climb up until the 50's methinks. Your defensive and offensive skills will absolutely suck and should you group at higher levels, be prepared to be rezzed constantly until your skills catch up to you. I won't drop everything in this post, but here's a route to consider for starters. 
<br />

<br />
I play a Wood-Elf Bard on Torv. Some say Half-elves are best, some go the human route for max exp. Tried the Vah Shir bit, but I absolutely hate Luclin, so I won't strat from there. 
<br />

<br />
As a Wood Elf Bard with 500k to spend, get yourself max AC and HP, plus buy as many Damage Shield items/potions that you can. I would get a Regen Breastplate as well for this self PL strat. 
<br />

<br />
Then go and purchase six 10-slot backpacks full of bone chips. Go find Gunlok Jore in North Kaladim. Be prepared to be there for awhile and have 2 weight reduction bags as well. Hand him 4 bone chips (hold the CTRL Key and position open bag near him, much easier). For every 4 chips you gain exp and an item. Once you run out of open slots, turn 180degrees and sell to the gal there. You will gain better exp than the Crushbone Belt Routine. I used this method to get my bazaar mule to gating capable. Around level 9 this will slow down a bit, but I have heard of folks going to 20+ with this method. Here's the link to Junlok:
<br />

<br />
http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=1823
<br />

<br />
You should be able to get to lvl 14 in a few hours this way. Remember, all of your skills are still at zero, but now you have training points to spend. 
<br />

<br />
Part of you gear should include Thunderous Drums of Karana (2.8mod percussion), best bang for the buck. If you want to work on some 1HB and piercing skills get a Troubadours Mace (1.8mod Brass) and a Battle Drummers Main Gauche (2.0mod Percussion) as well. If you can find a Lute of the Howler, you will be in good shape. I have not seen one sold since the EC /auction days, but then again, that may just be my server. In any case, a Primary Equipable Lute would be preferable. 
<br />

<br />
If you only go to level 14 this way, head to Oasis with Selo's and PoP Books, it should take no time at all. Then equip Regen BP, Damage Shields, Primary Equipable Lute, Troubadors Mace (for lvl18 tune when you get there and dual-wield). Songs to load up are:
<br />

<br />
lvl 5 Selo's (always)
<br />
lvl 6 Hymn of Restoration
<br />
lvl 2 Chords of Dissonance (don't go anywhere near NPCs)
<br />
lvl 7 Jonthan's Whistling Warsong
<br />
lvl 1 Chant of Battle
<br />

<br />
You will have to learn to twist your tunes. I suggest Hotkey banks and assign those keys to your NUM PAD
<br />

<br />
Run Around and Collect 4-5 MoBs. Test your regen. If you live through the fight with more than 50% health, you have found your soloing tactic for the next couple of levels. There may be better places to do this and you should know where from prior experience, I'm just giving and example. You should be able to keep 3 songs going at once. If you only have the Lute Equipped use lvl6 hymn for regen, lvl2 Chords for damage and lvl1 chant for AC.
<br />

<br />
Once you hit 16 or 17 go to LOIO and try your luck there near the river mouth. Always have Selo's ready in case you need to run. 
<br />

<br />
I did not have the luxury of nice gear, but am glad I've taken my time to get to where I am. With your bankroll, max Regen/HP/AC oughta get you to the 20's and then you can start some fear kiting, then chant kiting, then swarm kiting. 
<br />

<br />
That's my thoughts for now.
<br />

<br />
Wiladancer Eversing - Torv Board Troll</span></td>
