			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: hardcore 1-65 without 2-boxing<a name="28355"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 17 04 11:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Disclaimer: the following are my &quot;current&quot; feelings and thus my personal &quot;2 quarter notes to add to this bar&quot; and have no real meaning in the world whatsoever!  Unless you want them to. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Thunderous Drums of Karana (mostly for running, swarming, and pure chant kiting). Primary/Secondary usable.
<br />

<br />
Lute of the Howler, if availible.  Primary useable only.  Good for those AoE chants, as well as healing/mana songs.
<br />

<br />
Troubador's mace for Brass and 1hblunt.  Primary and Secondary usable.  Some haste songs require it.
<br />

<br />
Tear Shaped Ring, not as good (by a long shot) as LotH for stringed, BUT it means until you have your epic, always being able to sing a sting based song.
<br />

<br />
Blood Stained Flute for wind.  Primary usable only, high mod (2.2) for charming songs and invis.
<br />

<br />
Gear, from a recient post, Charisma rules!  Dex is good, too.  The higher your Charisma the less you miss notes (fail cast), and the better your chances of lulling, mez'n and charming mobs.  My current base Chr is 159, gonna be moving that up even higher now that I learned something new.
<br />

<br />
In the end, it is up to you.  Oh, main battle gouche, for peircing with percussion built in.  Great for mixing with the troubador's mace while mele'n and twisting songs to haste group as well as other things.  Might consider a fungi tunic for regen as that will keep your down time to a minimum.
<br />

<br />
Bards don't need mana like regular casters.  Even if you are totally out of mana, you are capable of putting out damage without engaging in mele.  Many bards will swarm kite til oom, then just chant kite (at lvl 52 I'm doing 4 dots throwing in Selo's when/if needed... I have run 3 now and regen 2) until mana is up again.  Oh, there is NOT ONE SPELL or SONG that regens our mana any faster.  However, FT gear works.  Get the earring of Solstice for mana regen.  And whatever else you feel would be good.  Cap is FT15.  (Errr Mana Regen 15... stupid change to make things easier to understand LOL)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
