				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, I used to post here but I haven't really since the switch from ezBoard but this really rubbed me the wrong way and I had to register.
<br />

<br />
Here's the facts korzon.
<br />

<br />
Yes, you can powerlevel yourself as far as you like in as little time as you wish, you can do that with any class. The catch with the bard is that there exists certain 'soft-skills' that you aquire when you REALLY play the class. You learn how to improvise, how to stay calm when the sh*t hits the fan and just generally...how to play the character.
<br />

<br />
My bard is my main, but I have powerleveled many other characters to at least 30 before starting to really play them. I believe this is something that can be done safely with most classes. My father for instance is interested in playing a bard but I have refused and explained why it's really a bad idea to PL a bard.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, you'll probably just blow me off as you have the others here. You'll powerlevel to 50 in a week or whatever and manage to get in a group, just on merit of being a bard. Then they'll realize that you suck...and ditch you...but this is your call.
<br />

<br />
The truth of the matter is, you'll never be a real bard...and you'll never be as good as me or most of the people here.
<br />

<br />
Enjoy your bard. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
