			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: hardcore 1-65 without 2-boxing<a name="28651"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 18 04 12:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>[/quote]Gear: You have 500k to equip yourself with.
<br />

<br />
What race would you choose?
<br />
What equipment will you buy?
<br />
And most importantly, where will you level?
<br />

<br />
I reckon it can be done in less than two days played, although you need to know the game inside and out and be very skillful to do that. [/quote]
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Sure, if I get to level 65 with any class without grouping at all, I'll be lacking some group skills.
<br />

<br />
But..
<br />

<br />
1. I see no reason why I would get a group killed.
<br />

<br />
2. I don't think it'll take more than a few days of grouping to get most of the grouping skills down. Of course there is always room for improvement, and I'll be hard pressed to compete with a bard whose been playing a bard for a few years.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
The race... I went with Vah Shir and am very happy with it.
<br />

<br />
With the 500k I would get gear that boosts your charisma as much as possible to decrease your missed notes and possibly increase the chances of getting a skill up.  For your weapon selection, who cares after mid 20s because you're going to level faster using songs and not trying to tank.  Also, get a selo horse when you get chants.
<br />

<br />
Where to hunt, I think you probably already have a good idea.  But with your chants and TDoK in hand, hop on your horse in an outdoor zone with lots of human sized mobs, like drolvs in FV and all you need to do is run in circles while chanting down mobs one at a time.  Find an area that is close to a bunch of the mobs but not subject many wonderers because you don't want to get stunned too many times.  Anyway, with the human sized mobs you'll be able to use autorun (num lock) and will only have to hold down your right or left turn button so you keep running in a tight circle.  You can go into a 3rd person view so can see what's around you while you go in circles and so you won't get dizzy. =)  Also, when your current target dies, hit tab (3rd person view still so you &quot;see&quot; the mobs) or whatever you have for target selection and chant down it down... repeat ad nauseum.
<br />

<br />
When you want to start killing giants, say seafury clops in OOT, you need to either make bigger circles by repeatedly tapping the right or left turn, or you can simply kite them in long stretches along the coast.  If you get an add and there's other peeps around, go in large circles while away from the peeps so they don't get the add(s).
<br />

<br />
Then a little later, when you can get into PoN, same thing, different critters.  Then a little later, go into PoV, same thing, different critters.
<br />

<br />
To get to 65 asap, you simply want zones with lots of stuff that won't take you too long to get into your kite circle, preferably someplace that you will get adds so you don't even have to break your circle... though you need to watch out for getting stunned, kinda important. =)  I'd be interested in knowing how fast you can do it.  Sure, you're going to be lacking in a lot of skills, but that's not what the challenge is.
<br />

<br />
I don't think you should group at all if you want to get 65 fast.  Groups will slow you down.  This isn't about getting a bard to 65 with maxxed skills is it?  If so then your /played isn't going to be as impressive because it takes a while to get all your skills up.  If you stick to chant kiting with the horse, your percussion will be fine and you can chant kite all the way to 65.  So, forget about getting your skills up and what to play in groups until afterwards, if you even want to continue with bard after you get 65.
<br />

<br />
Please post your /played once you get 65!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
