			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: hardcore 1-65 without 2-boxing<a name="28717"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 18 04 2:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Two days would be very hard to do.  Think about it that is over a level an hour.  Granted that the first 20 are gimmies that still leaves a level an hour.  Even if you did the next 30 in 15 hours (so say a total of 18 hours played) that leaves you 30 hours for 15 levels and these wont go by fast.  When you get past 56 you are looking at 20% exp/hour solo tops.  Even before 56 you are looking at 2.5 hours/level solo.   So,
<br />

<br />
18 hours to 50
<br />
15 hours to 56
<br />
45 hours to 65
<br />
--------------
<br />
78 hours total - looks like 3 days+ played minimum.
<br />

<br />
As far as race goes, with 500k it doesnt matter.  If you were starting from scratch you would want to go with a Vah Shir.  They can get a primary 2.0 lute that will make your life easier in your ae kiting days.
<br />

<br />
While it is an interesting experiment, and it is clearly something you enjoy doing, I dont think you will get a feel for what a Bard can and should do in a group.  That only comes with group experience and not just any group but a group that is challanged by their encounters.  A good bard can turn failure into success - but without being in those situations you cannot hope to understand what to do or how to pull it off.  Starting to learn this at 65 will get you or your group killed - especally if they dont know that you dont know what to do.
<br />

<br />
I will also disagree with another post in this thread that said you should not PL a bard.  A bards life drastically changes at around lvl 30.  Until then your impact on a group is fairly marginal.  Once you get mez and charm you become much more valuable to your group and your group is able to tackle things it couldnt before.  This is also the time you will learn the basics of the skills you will use much later in life. 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
